         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Gardens ¶ Brisbane 23rd Jany 1883 ¶ Baron Ferd. von Mueller K.C.M.G. &amp;c ¶ Melbourne ¶ Dear Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.01.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Pink</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M135, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ficus virgata</seg> var. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">virgata</seg> (MEL 2210752).</p>
               </note>Botanic Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Brisbane 23rd Jany 1883</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferd. von Mueller K.C.M.G. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to thank your for your letter of the 15th inst.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> together with the printed matter enclosed. By to-day's mail I have sent you a small box containing two flowers of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Nelumbium%20Leichhardti">Nelumbium Leichhardti</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not in APNI.</p>
               </note> &amp; a small fruit-bearing branchlet of the Ficus from Trinity Bay. There is no further variation in the leaves beyond that on the branch sent. It forms a very handsome umbrageous tree of semi-drooping habit, &amp; for beauty of habit &amp; foliage will form a rival to <name key="Ficus%20Benjaminia">Ficus Benjaminia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ficus Benjamina</seg>?</p>
               </note> It is perfectly distinct from all other kinds of Figs we have growing here. The propagator tells me the young plants were sent here by a Surveyor from Trinity Bay, they were kept in pots for some time, when two were planted out in the Gardens, &amp; are now about fifteen (15) feet high. Two years ago I had a bed trenched for one, which is now making splendid growth &amp; gradually developing into a very beautiful tree, &amp; Mr Bailey &amp; myself think it to be the handsomest variety of the kind we have.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to thank you my dear Baron for the compliment you have paid me in proposing to name it after me<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ficus pinkiana</seg>, named in B82.12.04, p. 273.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Pink</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Nelumbium%20Leichhardti">Nelumbium Leichhardti</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ficus%20Benjaminia">Ficus Benjaminia</name>
            </p>
